{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:proverbs.27",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 27,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 27 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.27.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:1",
      "text": "Do not boast about tomorrow, for you do not know what a day may bring forth.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.27.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:2",
      "text": "Let another praise you, and not your own mouth; a stranger, and not your own lips.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.27.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:3",
      "text": "A stone is heavy, and sand is weighty, but a fool's provocation is heavier than both.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.27.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:4",
      "text": "Wrath is cruel, anger is overwhelming; but who can stand before jealousy?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.27.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:5",
      "text": "Better is open rebuke than hidden love.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.27.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:6",
      "text": "Faithful are the wounds of a friend; profuse are the kisses of an enemy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.27.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:7",
      "text": "He who is sated loathes honey, but to one who is hungry everything bitter is sweet.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.27.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:8",
      "text": "Like a bird that strays from its nest, is a man who strays from his home.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.27.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:9",
      "text": "Oil and perfume make the heart glad, but the soul is torn by trouble.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.27.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:10",
      "text": "Your friend, and your father's friend, do not forsake; and do not go to your brother's house in the day of your calamity. Better is a neighbor who is near than a brother who is far away.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.27.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:11",
      "text": "Be wise, my son, and make my heart glad, that I may answer him who reproaches me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.27.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:12",
      "text": "A prudent man sees danger and hides himself; but the simple go on, and suffer for it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.27.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:13",
      "text": "Take a man's garment when he has given surety for a stranger, and hold him in pledge when he gives surety for foreigners.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.27.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:14",
      "text": "He who blesses his neighbor with a loud voice, rising early in the morning, will be counted as cursing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.27.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:15",
      "text": "A continual dripping on a rainy day and a contentious woman are alike;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.27.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:16",
      "text": "to restrain her is to restrain the wind or to grasp oil in one's right hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.27.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:17",
      "text": "Iron sharpens iron, and one man sharpens another.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.27.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:18",
      "text": "He who tends a fig tree will eat its fruit, and he who guards his master will be honored.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.27.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:19",
      "text": "As in water face answers to face, so the mind of man reflects the man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.27.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:20",
      "text": "Sheol and Abaddon are never satisfied, and never satisfied are the eyes of man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.27.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:21",
      "text": "The crucible is for silver, and the furnace is for gold, and a man is judged by his praise.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.27.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:22",
      "text": "Crush a fool in a mortar with a pestle along with crushed grain, yet his folly will not depart from him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.27.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:23",
      "text": "Know well the condition of your flocks, and give attention to your herds;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.27.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:24",
      "text": "for riches do not last for ever; and does a crown endure to all generations?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.27.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:25",
      "text": "When the grass is gone, and the new growth appears, and the herbage of the mountains is gathered,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.27.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:26",
      "text": "the lambs will provide your clothing, and the goats the price of a field;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.27.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:27",
      "text": "there will be enough goats' milk for your food, for the food of your household and maintenance for your maidens.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
